g could fold itself up, and time stand still.\n\n- Karen Tei Yamashita, Tropic of Orange\n|\nI love all things, not only the grand but the infinitely small: thimble, spurs, plates, flower vases.....\n\n- Pablo\n|\nMuch that for us is fraught with with happiness or misery, remains almost unnoticed by the rest of the world.\n\n- Marcel Proust, Jean Santeuil\n|\nThere are three qualities that every individual must have to achieve success: a Monk’s patience, a Warrior’s courage, a Child’s imagination.\n\n- Sharad\n|\nYesterday, the president met with a group he calls the coalition of the willing. Or, as the rest of the world calls them, Britain and Spain\n\n- Jon\n|\nConnect with someone on a deeper level…mentally, spiritually, emotionally…and your soul will transcend the height of ecstasy.\n\n- Carlos Wallace, The Other 99 T.Y.M.E.S: Train Your Mind to Enjoy Serenity\n|\nSo treasure your moments of happiness, the glimpses you see of truth, the nights you've been loved. That's all you've got.\n\n- Fay Weldon, Female Friends\n|\nI realized how truly hard it was, really, to see someone you love change right before your eyes. Not only is it scary, it throws your balance off as well.\n\n- Sarah Dessen, The Truth About Forever\n|\nListen for the call of your destiny, and when it comes, release your plans and follow.\n\n- Mollie\n|\nAlways remember, any book you haven’t read is still a new book.\n\n- Ann\n|\nThe human beings also passed canteens, which guards would fill with water. When food came in, the human beings were quiet and trusting and beautiful. They shared.\n\n- Kurt Vonnegut Jr., Slaughterhouse-Five\n|\nA poem is never a put-up job, so to speak. It begins as a lump in the throat, a sense of wrong, a homesickness, a lovesickness. It is never a thought to begin with.\n\n- Robert\n|\nLike the rudder or anchor on a ship, your habits can guide you in the direction of your dreams or hold you back and keep you from achieving them.\n\n- Mensah Oteh, The Good Life: Transform your life through one good day\n|\nThe Universe said, ‘Let me show your soul something beautiful.\n\n- Aberjhani, Elemental: The Power of Illuminated Love\n|\nNever stop exploring... with Mother Nature by your side, the possibilities are endless.\n\n- Cheryl Aguiar, Great Horned Owlets Rescue: Where There's a Will, There's a Way....\n|\nMost women would each be left with fewer dreams or without a dream, if the institution of marriage were to be abolished.\n\n- Mokokoma\n|\nIf your heart is conflicted, teach it to be unrestricted.\n\n- Nikki\n|\nThis place is a dream. Only a sleeper considers it real. Then death comes like dawn, and you wake up laughing at what you thought was your grief.\n\n- Jalaluddin\n|\nIf life is a flower, then love is the beauty of that flower.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nMy grandma said to me, Lailah; ‘You laugh while sleeping\n\n- Lailah\n|\nIf you are still alive, time is now, reject sin, seek righteousness.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nit was the kind of moonthat I would want to send back to my ancestorsand gift to my descendantsso they know that I too,have been bruised...by beauty.\n\n- Sanober  Khan, Turquoise Silence\n|\nThe darker the night, the brighter the stars,  The deeper the grief, the closer is God!\n\n- Fyodor Dostoyevsky, Crime and Punishment\n|\nKindness, I’ve discovered, is everything in life.\n\n- Isaac\n|\nBeing brave means that knowing when you fail, you won't fail forever.\n\n- Lana\n|\nWhen you love, you forgive; when you forgive, you love.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nThe sacred is discovered in what moves and touches us, in what makes us tremble.\n\n- Sam\n|\nOnce you reject fear, you will become the perfect candidate to receive and reflect Truth.\n\n- Suzy Kassem, Rise Up and Salute the Sun: The Writings of Suzy Kassem\n|\nEnjoy the beauty, love and peace of a sacred Christmas.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nLook into my eyes andYou'll see my mind.A tranquil city,That rebuilt itself and left the past behind.\n\n- Innocent Mwatsikesimbe, This Is My Life\n|\nYou can’t selectively numb your anger, any more than you can turn off all lights in a room, and still expect to see the light.\n\n- Shannon\n|\nWhile we mortals fumble through ambiguity, he never loses his harmony #MyExperiencewith498A\n\n- Ravi Ranjan, My Experience with 498A: Are all marriages made in heaven?\n|\nMy house burned downBut anyway, it was afterThe flower petals had already fallen\n\n- Tachibana\n|\nStart writing by thinking, not wrestling with words.\n\n- Jonathan Price, Put That in Writing\n|\nTruth is not fully explosive, but purely electric. You don't blow the world up with the truth; you shock it into motion.\n\n- Criss Jami, Healology\n|\nHere’s to freedom, cheers to art. Here’s to having an excellent adventure and may the stopping never start.\n\n- Jason\n|\nAdversity, if for no other reason, is of benefit, since it is sure to bring a season of sober reflection. People see clearer at such times. Storms purify the atmosphere.\n\n- Henry\n|\nWith which stars do they go on speaking,the rivers that never reach the sea?\n\n- Pablo Neruda, The Book of Questions"